    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Flat-bottomed boats with a straight falling stern and a short forecastle. These are known to be used as fishing vessels on the Schelde River from the thirteenth to the 19th century.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
